# Supabase project credentials, used for real user sign-up/sign-in and profile storage.
# Get these from your Supabase project: Project Settings > API.
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is the public "anon" key — safe to ship in the client bundle,
# access is enforced server-side by the Row Level Security policies in supabase/schema.sql.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Web3Forms access key, used by the contact form to actually deliver submissions to
# an inbox. Get one free at https://web3forms.com — it's meant to be public/client-side
# (that's the whole point of the service), protected by their own spam filtering and
# optional domain restriction, not by keeping it secret.
VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=
